cope, the biases introduced by baryonic effects are\nmuch more significant. We show that this mitigation technique significantly\nreduces the biases for such larger surveys, but that a more effective\nmitigation strategy will need to be developed in order ensure that the residual\nbiases in these surveys fall below the statistical errors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Dec 2012 21:07:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
